inn1.comm: fuller length on middle. Jamshed tries to work this away square on the leg side
length ball pitching just outside off. Defended to the bowler
fuller length just outside off. Defended to the off side
fuller length, wide outside off. Jamshed leans into it and drives through extra-cover to open his account with a boundary
back of a length on middle and Jamshed plays this to the leg side
back of a length on middle and Jamshed squirts this square on the off side for a single
back of a length on the pads and Jamshed glances this towards backward square leg for a couple
back of a length outside off and defended back to the bowler
length ball on middle and off. Defended to the leg side
back of a length outside off. Defended to the bowler
length ball outside off and Nasir hangs his bat, with no movement of the feet, and almost gets an edge on it as it carries through to the keeper. Nasir livin la vida loca here with this technique
length ball on and around off. Steered to backward point for none.
fuller length on off stump. Defended to the off side
length ball on off stump. Defended again to the off side. Shehzad solid in defense
length ball drifting down the pads. Called wide by the umpire
back of a length outside off. Defended towards cover
length ball on off stump. Defended to the bowler
fuller length outside off and shaping away slightly from the batsman. Shehzad hangs his bat as the ball rushes past

fuller length on off stump and Shehzad opens the face to steer to point. However, point makes a hasty throw at the non-strikers, and the batsmen end up running on the overthrow. Wasteful from Zimbabwe, was simply not required after a superb over from Panyangara
length ball outside off. Looks like a slower ball. Left alone by the batsman
wide delivery outside off and immediately 'wided' by the umpire
length ball outside off and Shehzad gets on the back foot to cut behind square for a boundary
short ball outside off. Shehzad attempts a pull shot, but misses the ball entirely. Looked like a slower ball change up from Shingi
fuller length on middle and leg. Shehzad plays this one under his eyes and the pair set off for a quick single
short of a length pitching outside off. Jamshed plays a half-hearted pull that lobs up in the air and lands just in front of mid on. Risky shot from the opener
fuller length outside off. Defended to the off side
fuller length outside off and swinging away. Shehzad content to let it through
fuller length again, outside off and shaping away. Left alone by Shehzad
short of a length outside off. Defended behind to point
length ball on middle and leg. Defended to the bowler
fuller length outside off and Shehzad content to leave it through to the keeper
wider delivery outside off and full. Left alone by Shehzad. Completes a maiden over for Panyangara
fuller length outside off. Defended to the off side
short of a length on middle and leg. Jamshed tries to whip this away square on the leg side, but fails to make a connection
fuller delivery on the pads and Jamshed able to work this away to deep backward square leg
fuller length wide off the leg stump and called a wide
fuller length on and around off. Shehzad drives this straight to a diving mid off, who is able to get a hand on it, and deflect it towards long on to recover
short of a length outside off and defended to the off side
short of a length outside off. Defended to the off side
fuller length on middle and leg. Jamshed clips this through square leg for a boundary
length ball outside off. Jamshed angles this through the point region for a single
fuller length outside off. Shehzad gets a thick deflection that evades the grasp of second slip. Not a dropped chance but still went in the general vicinity. Ends up being recovered by third man
length ball outside off and defended to the bowler
fuller length outside off and defended solidly
length ball on and around off. Defended to the leg side
fuller length outside off and defended to mid on
length ball on and around off. Defended to the leg side

length ball on middle and leg. Worked away by Shehzad towards mid on. Shehzad timed this well, a little too well as mid on picked up on the chance and threw at the non-striker's end. Shehzad makes his ground in time
back of a length delivery on the stumps, Jamshed stays back and defends it
short of a length as Jamshed gets a thick leading edge on it, ballooning over a diving backward point as it is recovered by sweeper cover
fuller length delivered on middle and defended to mid on
length ball on and around off. Defended to cover
length ball outside off and Shehzad dances down the track to heave this through midwicket for a boundary. Good intent from Shehzad, as some pressure is now released
fuller length on off and defended to the off side
short ball outside off and Shehzad uses his feet to try and force a shot through the off side, but is unable to get it away
length ball on middle and leg. Jamshed works this through midwicket for a couple
full again on the pads and Jamshed clips this away square on the leg side
length ball outside off and defended to the bowler
full delivery, wide of off stump. Jamshed drills this through cover, but finds the fielder. It was sweetly timed and Jamshed was unlucky not to find the gap
length ball outside off and guided to second slip for none
length ball outside off and played straight to mid off
short of a length on the pads and Jamshed glances this for a single
length ball outside off and beats the edge of Shehzad's bat on its way to the keeper
fuller length just outside off. Defended to mid off
length ball outside off and Jamshed gets into position quickly, heaving this over mid on for a much-needed boundary
short ball on leg and Jamshed hooks this to fine leg
length ball outside off. Chopped by Shehzad, who is fortunate not to chop it on to his stumps, as the ball is squeezed to fine leg
back of a length outside off. Defended to the off side
length ball on the pads and Jamshed glances this to square leg

length ball on middle and the pads. Jamshed clips this square on the leg side. Zimbabwe should focus on a line outside off, as this is far too straight for Jamshed, as he is comfortably working away the deliveries
short of a length on middle and Shehzad squared up by the line of the delivery. Gets a leading edge and luckily misses the man at gully
length ball outside off. Defended to the bowler

dropped short ball on middle and off. Jamshed gets back and hooks this towards fine leg. Chatara, who is stationed there, gets two hands on it, but ends up helping it on its way for a six. Good effort from the seamer
slower ball, full and outside off. Jamshed steers this through the third man region for a couple
short ball on off stump. Rushes Jamshed into a hasty pull shot that lands comfortably on the leg side
fuller length on middle and off. Defended to the leg side
same line again and this time Jamshed works this behind square for a hesitant run
length outside off and Shehzad steps back to open up space on the off side as he steers this through extra-cover
fuller length on middle and off. Defended to the leg side
length ball on and around off. Defended back to the bowler
fuller length, pitching outside off. Shehzad steps back and cuts this in front of point for a couple
short ball pitched on leg stump. Jamshed moved across so was not in line to play that ball, and the umpire, gauging that, ends up calling it wide. A tad harsh methinks
almost the same line and length again, this time Jamshed stays his ground and glances this fine to fine leg
short ball wide of off stump. Shehzad cuts this square on the off side. Could have done more with that
fuller length pitching outside off. Jamshed looking to drive this through extra-cover, but ends up hitting it back to the bowler
fuller length outside off. Jamshed leans into a drive through extra-cover
fuller length drifting down the pads. Called wide by the umpire
length ball outside off and Ahmed content to shoulder arms
length ball outside off and Shehzad defends to gully
length ball on middle and leg. Worked away to the leg side by Jamshed
length ball outside off. Shehzad backs away to cut but the ball beats the outside edge
full outside off. Defended to the off side
straight one on middle. Defended to the bowler
length ball on middle and leg. Shehzad tries to work this away in front of square on the leg side. Some confusion from the batsmen as they attempt a run, but end up aborting it
fuller delivery on middle and off. Defended to the off side
length ball on leg and Jamshed glances this square on the leg side. Williams, rushing in from midwicket, is able to intercept a certain boundary
fuller length on middle and off. Played straight to mid off
fuller length outside off and Jamshed, looking to drive through extra-cover, gets a thick edge on its way to the keeper. Gives away a useful start as Zimbabwe strike for the first time this morning
fuller length delivery on off, Hafeez drives it back to the bowler
length ball outside off. Hafeez content to shoulder arms
length ball outside off. Played directly to point
length ball on off and Shehzad cuts this square on the off side
fuller length on off. Defended to the off side
length ball on and around off. Shehzad works this away through mid off
length ball on and around off. Hafeez uses his feet to dance down and drive to long off
fired in full on off, Shehzad eases it down to long off
turning in from outside off, Hafeez defends it back to the bowler
turning in from outside off, Hafeez defends it back to the bowler
fuller length outside off. Driven to the off side for none
length ball outside off and angling in. Shehzad shoulders arms
short of a length outside off. Defended to the off side
short ball drifting down the leg side. Shehzad unable to get anything on it as its called wide by the umpire
short ball outside off. Shehzad steers to gully for none
short ball outside off and angling in. Defended to point
fuller length on off stump. Steered to long off for a single
length ball on off and Shehzad gets on the back foot to drive through long off
length ball on middle and Hafeez dances down but ends up defending to the off side
fuller length on middle and leg. Hafeez able to work it away to mid on
fuller length on middle and defended to the bowler
keeps it full on off, Shehzad pushes it towards mid off
shorter length on middle and off. Cut square on the off side
length ball wide of off stump. Shehzad unlucky to find gully as he looks for the gap through third man
fuller length, drifting down the pads, Shehzad fails to get bat on it, but ends up getting a leg-bye
short of a length outside off and angling in. Hafeez content to let it through to the keeper
length ball outside off. Defended to the off side
short of a length outside off and Hafeez shoulders arms
full on middle, driven down for a single after a misfield from the bowler
short of length on off, pushed to midwicket
on length on off, cut to point
short of length on leg, turns further down and clips the pad on the way
short and wide, cut on off and the fielder at points dives to save the single
short of length on the pads, turned away on the leg side towards long-on
length ball outside off, left alone by Hafeez
on length again and wider outside off, left for the keeper
on length outside off, angling in, defended on the front foot
shorter and wider, Hafeez has room and cuts it hard fine, well away from third man for four
short of length outside off, left alone
short of length on off, turned to deep midwicket for a single
length ball on off, defended back
on length on middle, defended on leg
slightly slighted on leg, turned to deep midwicket and Hafeez is still in pain
on length on the pads, steered to midwicket for a quick single
short of length on middle and leg, turned to short fine leg
on the pads, tucked to square leg for a single
on length outside off, Shehzad leans forward and defends
full on off, driven down the ground to mid-off
short of length outside off, Shehzad goes back and pulls it wide of mid-on for two
short and well outside off, Shehzad pulls again but can't time it very well this time, only a single to mid-on
short of length outside off, it was angled in, Misbah defended it but missed it
length ball on off and middle, defended back to the bowler
slightly full on leg, swept to deep fine leg for two
full outside off and pushed down on off for a quick single by the time cover gets there
length ball outside off, Misbah goes back and defends
full on off, turned to midwicket
length ball outside off, defended on off towards point
tossed up slightly outside off, turned on leg again for another dot
short and wide outside off, Shehzad goes back and cuts it square wide of point. Fielder had to dive int he del and they took three
on length on off, defended back
tossed up on middle, defended back to Williams
full on off, drive to cover
full on off, Misbah made room on off and only pushed towards point, Shehzad was a long way down but came back just in time at non-striker's
on length on middle, turned to midwicket off the back foot
on length outside off, pushed to point
short of length outside off, cut straight to backward point
on length outside off, guided to point again
slightly fuller and wider, Shehzad drives it square past point and they get two
full on middle, driven back to the bowler
full on middle and leg, driven ton long-off. Just three from the over and 100 is up for Pakistan
short of length on middle, Shehzad goes back and defends
tossed up on off, turns away a bit and it's guided to short third man
full on off, Misbah makes room and his is off the mark with a drive to long-off
short of length on middle and leg, pushed down to long-on
on length on middle, pushed back to the bowler
short and wide, cut to sweeper cover for a single
short of length outside off, Misbah defends it awkwardly towards cover
full and wide, Shehzad swings his arms to drive it over the infield but it's only a single
short of length on off, pushed down towards mid-on
on length on off, defended in the crease
short of length outside off, Misbah tried to run it down to third man with a jab but missed it
on length on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler. Just two from the over
short of length on off, Shehzad goes back and cuts it past point
on length on off, Misbah makes rom but can't get it past point
tossed up on leg from wide of the crease, driven down to long-on
on length outside off, cut straight to backward point
full on off, driven down to long-off
short of length outside off, cut after making room to deep point
on length on middle, turned to midwicket
on length on off, inside edge goes on the leg side
on length well outside off, Misbah drives but some away movement misses the bat
on length on off, Misbah moves towards the off stump but can't middle it again, he's struggling to rotate the strike here
on length off, defended back to the bowler
slower and wide outside off, Misbah cuts it to backward point and it's a maiden
short of length outside off, Shehzad waits for it and cuts it late fine past the keper for four. There's nobody in the deep
full on middle and leg, Shehzad swept it and a leading edge went just over short fine leg. Had he moved a couple of steps back in time, the catch might have been taken
full on the pads, Shehzad tries to sweep but can't middle it
over the wicket, full on off, driven down to long-off
round the wicket, full on leg, defended back
full on middle, Misbah comes down to convert it into a full toss and drives it to long-on
short of length outside off, cut to point where the fielder dives to his right but they take one

full outside off, and Shehzad has fallen under pressure in the deep. He drove it and took the aerial route but didn't get the distance and Sikander Raza at long-off runs to his right and takes a good catch
full outside off, driven through covers, Amin off the mark straightaway
short of length on middle, Misbah defends
short of length on off, defended back to the bowler again
short of length on off, Misbah went back to defend and the inside edge went quite close to the stumps
full and flighted outside off, driven down the ground for a single
short of length on off, Misbah goes back, makes room and cuts it sweeper cover
on middle, Amin goes back to drive it to long-on
tossed up on leg, Misbah makes room on off and slog-sweeps it  for a four to the midwicket boundary. He didn't middle it, but it had enough to go all the way
flighted on off, driven after making room to cover. A misfield, but they don't go for the single
full on off, driven down to long-off makes it eight from the over
on length outside off, cut straight to point
on length outside off, it nipped in a bit and bounced, Misbah gets an outside edge to third man
on length outside off, driven square to point
on length outside off, cut off the back foot to third man
on length on off, defended on the off side
on length on off and middle, Misbah tries to work it on leg but misses
short of a length pitching in and around off. Umar drills this straight to short cover
back of a length delivery outside off, Amin cuts it away square of the wicket on the off side
length ball on the pads and Misbah glances this behind square
fuller length pitching outside off and Umar gets an edge behind square
short of a length on middle and off. Defended back to the bowler
slower ball outside off and at a length. Misbah adjusts last second to play this through cover for a single
full and angling in, Misbah-ul-Haq drives it down to long on
full delivery on middle and Umar drives this towards extra-cover
length ball drifting down the pads. Misbah has stepped back to make room on the off side, but ended up letting it go for a wide
flighted delivery outside off, Misbah-ul-Haq drives it to cover
full delivery right at the pads. Defended to the bowler
fuller length on middle and off. Defended to the off side
short of a length pitching outside off and angling in. Misbah works this away through midwicket
short of a length on middle and off. Umar goes for the pull but doesn't get any connection with the ball
length ball outside off and with width offered, Umar has a flash that beats a diving backward point on the way to a boundary near fine leg
length ball on middle and off. Umar plays a swivel pull square on the leg side
short of a length outside off and angling in. Misbah able to steer this through the leg side for a quick single

rank delivery from Chatara, was going down the leg side and for all appearances was going to be a wide, but Umar adjusts his body to get inside of the line and help it on its way to the fine leg boundary. Bonus runs for Pakistan here
fuller delivery outside off and cut away to point
fuller length, closer into the batsman. Misbah works this away through long on
full delivery, almost a full toss, as Umar drives on the up through the gap in the covers. Fielder is able to stop it before reaching the boundary
turning into the pads, Misbah-ul-Haq works it away to deep square leg
fuller length on middle and off. Umar clips this through midwicket for a well-timed boundary
length ball on middle and off. Umar steers this towards cover before setting off for a quick single
short ball on middle and off. Umar plays a pull towards deep backward square
length ball outside off. Misbah plays this under his eyes and gets Umar back on strike
short of a length pitching outside off. Umar plays this towards the off side for a single
short of a length on off and middle. Misbah works this away towards mid on
length ball on the pads and Umar tries to glance this behind square but fails to connect
length ball on middle and off. Umar pulls this through midwicket
fuller length and Umar shuffles down to play a lovely lofted shot through extra-cover for a boundary

length ball on middle and leg. Prosper falls sharply to his left to hold on to a sharp return chance. Excellent response from Utseya after Amin signalled his intent. Timely wicket for Zimbabwe, as Umar goes for a promising cameo of 33 off 25 balls. In walks the master of disaster, the incomparable, Shahid Afridi
short of a length outside off and Afridi gets deep in the crease to work this square on the leg side for a single to get off the mark
length ball outside off and Misbah gets into position for a reverse sweep but fails to get anything on the ball
pitched up on middle, Misbah-ul-Haq shuffles forward and glances it to square leg
length ball on off stump and Misbah backs away to create room before cutting this towards extra-cover
wide ball outside off and Misbah steers this behind square on the off side for a single
short ball on off and middle. Shahid plays a pull through square leg
short of a length outside off. Misbah steps into the line and then opens the face to steer this through the off side
short ball on middle and slanting in sharply. Afridi able to squeeze this through backward point
length ball outside off. Misbah plays this to the off side
fuller length outside off and Misbah works this away to long on for a single
length delivery on off, Misbah-ul-Haq comes forward to drive, edges it onto his body and the ball rolls away to the off side
short of a length outside off. Misbah steers this through mid on
short ball on middle and off. Afridi pulls this between square leg and midwicket
short of a length and Misbah backs away to work it through the off side
short of a length, slow bouncer, and Afridi adjusts to cut this behind square for a single
length ball outside off and Misbah steers this through midwicket
full delivery wide of off stump. Misbah, with the intent of hitting over cover, ends up hitting his behind square and over gully for a much-needed boundary
short of a length and width offered. Misbah gets into position quickly to cut this away in the gap between gully and point for a four
length ball outside off and Misbah dances down to try and heave Chatara over extra-cover, but ends up missing the ball entirely
short of a length outside off and again Misbah steps down but fails to connect

short of a length outside off and Misbah pulls this square on the leg side with a lofted shot as Malcolm Waller bailed on an opportunity to go for the catch, opting instead to save the extra runs. Could be costly for Zimbabwe as Misbah is dangerous at the back-end of an innings

short of a length outside off and without moving his feet Afridi has a waft at it and ends up getting a thick edge on the way to the keeper. This could hurt Pakistan's chances of a competitive total, while Zimbabwe will like their chances even more
short ball on middle and leg. Misbah glances to the leg side
length ball on middle and leg. Ahmed nudges this through midwicket for one and gets off the mark
short ball on middle and Misbah steps back to make room, but ends up finding the fielder
fuller length delivery on off, Misbah-ul-Haq clips it off his pads to deep mid wicket for a well-run couple
short of a length on the pads and Misbah plays a lovely hook shot through fine leg. Just one run short of yet another fifty from the Pakistan captain
fuller delivery again on the pads and Misbah steps back and plays a lovely drive through extra-cover to bring up his 11th fifty this year. Can we say well-paced innings?
short of a length outside off and Ahmed gets forward to hammer this through midwicket. Looked a certain boundary, but ended up slowing in the outfield
short of a length outside off and Ahmed cuts this square on the off side for another couple
wide delivery on the off side and full. Ahmed gets down on one knee to blitz this through midwicket for another boundary

short of a length on off and middle. Ahmed, who is looking to play a hook shot, slows the down stroke so it gets a thick edge over the keeper to the boundary where no one is stationed. Fortuitous shot from the Pakistan wicketkeeper
fuller delivery and this time Ahmed works him away through mid on
fuller delivery on the pads and Misbah squirts this square on the off side for a single and retains the strike
slower ball on middle and leg. Misbah works this away through midwicket for a couple
full delivery on middle and Misbah makes room before getting down on one knee and driving this square through the off side to bring up a boundary
full delivery angling down the pads. Misbah nudges this to midwicket for a pair
short of a length on middle and off. Misbah pulls this behind square but finds the fielder soon after. Misbah admonishes himself for not finding the boundary
full delivery on middle and leg. Ahmed pushes this through midwicket. Misbah wants two but Ahmed sends him back
fuller delivery outside off and Misbah gets down once again on one knee and hammers this through midwicket for a boundary.
length ball on the off stump and Ahmed squeezes this behind square on the off side

slower ball on middle and leg. Misbah fails to connect as he makes room to work it away through the off side. Ahmed makes a dash in anticipation but then sees the bowler pick up the ball to throw down the non-striker's end. Ahmed, who looks as though he is getting in the way of the throw, is able to get in on time. The Zimbabweans go up to appeal the decision, as it looks as though Ahmed was getting in the way, but the umpires finally decree that it is still not out. Interesting one there as it looked blatant.
back of a length delivery outside off, Misbah-ul-Haq heaves it away to deep mid wicket
slower delivery outside off, Ahmed drives it away to deep extra cover, the deep fielder did well to stop it
short of a length on and around off. Ahmed tries to clear mid on, and almost reaches long on, but falls just short
full toss on the pads and Misbah tries to clip this square on the leg side, but misses the ball, and lets out a cry in anguish at a failed opportunity to convert
slower delivery outside off, Ahmed heaves it across the line to deep mid wicket
length ball wide of off stump. Ahmed tries to find the gap on the off side, but finds point
delivery straying down the pads and called a wide. Misbah did move back, but was still going wide

wide delivery down the pads, and a full toss. Misbah once again backs away and tries to play a pickup shot over midwicket which goes higher than farther. Fielder, running in from deep midwicket, is unable to hold on to the chance. Close call from the Pakistan captain
full delivery on leg and Ahmed, trying to squirt it through the off side, ends up getting an edge which just carries to Brendan Taylor behind. Good low catch
full delivery outside off. Hafeez steps to the ball and plays a paddle sweep that just misses backward square leg
full delivery on middle and leg. Hafeez able to clip this away through square leg
full delivery on off and Hafeez waits on the back foot before heaving through extra-cover for a boundary
slower ball wide of off stump. Hafeez smashes this into the deep at extra-cover
dropped full delivery on the pads and Hafeez chips this over midwicket. Raza, running in from deep midwicket, gets to it, but ends up bobbling the ball when he falls over. Another dropped chance!

it is not often you get a second straight chance at redemption. This time Misbah, who had crossed with Hafeez the previous ball, hits it straight in the same area, except this one is higher than flatter. Raza settles in under it, and completes the catch
short ball wide off the leg stump and, more importantly, allows Hafeez to cross over for the last to balls of the innings
full toss going down the leg side and, even though Hafeez goes after it, still too wide for him to connect. Shingi needs to keep it together here

slower ball wide of off stump and Hafeez waits patiently before cutting in front of square. That was definitely a 'ok will lose the pace and get it in the right place' kind of delivery that was begging to be slammed out of the ground
full delivery on middle and leg. Hafeez tucks this away through midwicket, and is able to scamper home for the second run

inn2.comm: Oh, that's a great start. Right up there on the toes of the batsman and he digs it out just in time

huge appeal here. The ball took off from short of a length and the batsman was looking to nudge it down to fine leg. The keeper collects it and goes up straight away, but the umpire is not interested.
more lift from Irfan. This time he targets the off side corridor. The batsman drops his wrists and the ball goes safely to the keeper
fuller this time and it's clipped from the crease to midwicket
nice inviting length from Irfan and Masakadza leans forward and pushes to cover
shorter and down the leg side and Masakadza clips it behind square on the leg side, the fielder at fine leg was slow to start and midwicket cleans up
full toss on middle, punched right back to the bowler to end the over
nice flight and the batsman defends it down the ground
on off stump, Masakadza comes forward and blocks it to the off side
shorter, goes back and punches down to mid-on
oh, a leading edge as the batsman goes back to defend it but it is wide of slip.
fullish just outisde off and he carves it out to point
full and on middle driven strongly down the ground
just back of a length and seaming away a little. Masakadza stays back to hit to over
short, rising deliverry outside off and is guided to point off the back foot
goes fuller this time, and a little slower too. Rolls his fingers over the top of it and Masakadza pushes it back down the ground

oh, loads of bounce there. too much for the keeper to handle. This one rears off the short of a length as Irfan angles it across the right hander. The batsman leaves it alone but the bounce takes it all the way past the keeper and to the third man boundary
more bounce for Irfan as the punch it to cover goes off the splice of the bat
angled across and he opens the face to guide it to point. The batsman seek a single, but the fielder is too quick
comes forward and drives this full ball on off stump to point again
comes down the track and nudges it to the cover field and takes off for a quick single
flatter trajectory and he moves back to slap it down to long-on
comes forward to this tossed up ball and clips it to midwicket

oh, he's fallen to the only man out there in the deep. The ball was there to be hit, but Sibanda doesn't get the power he wanted. Nice, flighted ball from Hafeez and he goes down on one knee to slog sweep it. Umar Amin runs around and pulls out the slide to hold on to a good catch. Zimbabwe lose their first
oh, outside edge. he goes back to work it to the leg side but the ball takes a thick edge and goes down to third man
swept and placed perfectly between the fielder at short fine and square leg. Fullish ball on middle gets the treatment. Good intent from Taylor
oh, he's beaten. Short of a length and rising as has been Irfan's wont in this spell. Masakadza hopes to defend it off the back foot but the ball seams away and sails past his outside edge
flash and miss. Short ball, more than enough room but Masakadza's cut shot does not connect
targets the stumps with a fullish ball. the batsman gets in front of the line of the ball and defends it solidly
cuts this short ball outside off straight to cover
Irfan goes tighter as this one is around the off stump corridor on a back of a length. Masakadza uses soft hands to dab it out to point
short ball, rising up toward his chest but Masakadza swivels on his back foot but his pull is mistimed as it goes in the air and just wide of the leg gully
shorter ball on the stumps and its punched off the back foot to midwicket
Oh, good shot. He knows its the Powerplay and there's no one down at deep fine leg. Immediately goes down on one knee to this ball angled just a tad down leg and gets good reward.
and Hafeez makes the adjustment, going shorter and its pushed down to long-on
more runs off the sweep shot for Zimbabwe. this one was off a top edge as Taylor goes for the fine sweep to this fullish ball on the stumps
goes back and pushes it to long-on
shorter and angled into the pads, he picks it off to fine leg
back of a length just outside off and its blocked off the back foot
full and on the stumps, Masakadza digs it out back to the bowler
sways out of the line of this shortish ball and watches it go into the keeper's hands
Irfan's testing the middle of the pitch here. Short ball given the same treatment as Masakadza evades the line of the ball quite easily
the fuller ball has been a variation for Irfan through this spell and its back again as the batsman defends it back to the bowler
he's strayed too far down leg. Masakadza was looking to make some room for himself and he's duped Irfan to bowl a short ball further wide
Crunch! That's a powerful pull shot, right off the middle. He was still at the crease this time and with his weight on the back foot, pulls the short ball on middle off to the midwicket boundary
gets into the straps striaght away. Lovely line and length, just a hint of away movement as well and Taylor lets it go to the keeper
comes forward and pushes this full ball on off out to cover
the punch to cover is off the back foot this time as Junaid goes shorter. Taylor pulls the top hand off the bat after completing the shot
back of a length and he stays still at the crease and pushes it out to the off side
good accuracy from Junaid. Ties down the batsman refusing him any room. This one is on middle, just back of a length and gets the back foot defence as reply
and Junaid starts with a maiden. back of a length and angled away. Taylor powers it off the back foot but it goes only as far as the man at cover
Masakadza follows this short ball but can't make much of the room provided as the bounce beats him once again
draws him onto the front foot this time and all his tentative forward push meets is air as the ball goes on to the keeper
oh, he strays on the pads this time after building such good pressure. Clipped to the leg side for a single
and he's greeted with a short ball which is nicely negotiated. Taylor goes back and uses soft hands to ride the bounce and drop it on the off side
draws the batsman forward but the line is wrong as he clips it off to midwicket. The ball was in the air for a little while, but it was nowhere near the fielder
back of a length on middle and he goes back to work it on the leg side but the ball only takes the inside edge
fullish and at the stumps as the batsman comes forward to push it back to the bowler

oh, what a catch! No, wait, Hafeez is not calling it. He wants the third umpire's opinion on this. Beautiful ball, angled across the batsman and seams just that bit away to get Masakadza's edge. Hafeez at first slip dives full length to his right and gets hold of the ball, but as he hits the ground it pops out. Great effort from Hafeez nonetheless
keeps it full around the off stump and the batsman meets the ball on his front foot and pushes it down to mid-off

oh my God, he's nailed this. Junaid gets a little carried away with his length and bowls a half volley that is in the slot for Masakadza to get onto the front foot and slam it over the bowlers head for a thumping boundary
and there's the effect of the last ball. Junaid drops short and it sits up for Masakadza who was waiting on his back foot and pulls it over the square leg boundary. Brilliant batting from the opener
better length and line from Junaid as he returns back around the off stump corridor and Masakadza pushes it harmlessly into the off side
Taylor charges him but he only manages to hit it back to the bowler
stays in his crease and works this shorter ball on middle down to long-on
shorter and flatter again and it's punched down the ground

and Rehman does the trick in his first over. He tosses this one up much more than the previous balls. Masakadza's eyes light up as he comes down the  track but he plays across the line, looking to clip it towards midwicket. The ball grips, turns and leaves Masakadza stranded in the middle of the wicket as Sarfraz does the rest
angled down the leg side, he moves back and flicks it fine and the ball looks good to head to the boundary but the fielder pulls out a timely boot.
flatter ball again, on middle this time and its pushed down the ground
Lovely shot, picks this one off his legs and puts it away off the back foot square on the leg side for another boundary. Zimbabwe are picking up the pace here.

oh there's another edge, but it falls short of first slip. It's a nice line, inviting that waft outside off stump and Taylor too the bait, but played it softly enough not to carry. But the ball hits Hafeez on the inside of the knee and he grimaces in pain
short of a length on middle and he pushes it back down the ground off the back foot
angles this fullish ball across the batsman, who goes back and shoulders arms
hits him on the pads as the batsman looks to work it to the leg side. Junaid goes up in appeal but the ball keeping with the fullish length he has bowled has pitched well outside leg stump
he's at the stumps again and Taylor this time gets bat on it as he moves back and turns it down to midwicket
Comes nicely forward to smother any turn and defends it back to the bowler
pushes it out to the off side off the front foot

terrible fielding there from the uber-tall Mohammad Irfan. The ball is at Taylor's pads and he nudges it in the air to fine leg where Irfan presents the perfect bridge for the ball to sneak through and go off to the boundary
full on leg stump and he nudges it just wide of fine leg
comes forward and defends it to the off side
fulllish ball, but Raza goes back to punch it square on the on side but he only gets an inside edge
Room given and gleefully accepted by Taylor as he plays a flowing extra cover drive. The fielder at mid-off dives in an attempt to stop it but it is too well timed. Imperious shot from Taylor
overcompesates on the line as he strays on the pads and is flicked square on the leg side for a single
that's better. Back of a length and uses the left-armer's angle to square him up as the ball takes the shoulder of the bat and squirts off to point
shortish ball allows the batsman to jump on his back foot and work it into midwicket region

digs it in, but the angle takes it across the batsman and Raza wants nothing to do with it. It doesn't get the bounce Irfan could manage and it wasn't targeting the batsman but it does keep him in check
Raza is moving across the stumps and he could have been in danger there. This was full and straight and if he hadn't got bat on that he would have been plumb.
good drift from Rehman. Pushes it on middle and turns it across the batsman. Taylor defends it carefully off the backfoot
Oh, and he gets dip this time to beat Taylor's defence. The keeper goes up in appeal straight away but Rehman is slow to join and the umpire is unmoved. He needs a slip
full ball on the off stump, pushed down to long-off
full on middle and he blocks it easily

direct hit! And guess who it is. Misbah-ul-Haq has got rid of his opposite number. Raza leans into a push-drive to the covers and sets off, but hesitates a little bit which causes just enough confusion for Misbah to hare around, grab the ball and hit the bulls-eye.
on length outside of, driven down to long-off
on length on off, turned to square leg
on length on middle, steered to square leg again
tossed up outside off, defended on the front foot
short of length outside off, cut fine on off behind square
on length on off, turning in, defended on the back foot
given straightaway! It pitched on length just outside off, Raza went back to defend but missed and was struck right in front of the stumps after turning. Four down now Zimbabwe
short of length on off, steered to backward square leg after the turn
short of length on off, pushed past cover for a single
flatter one, short of length outside off and driven to sweeper cover
on length outside off, driven with soft hands after leaning forward and it's gone fine past short third man for four
on length on middle, defended back

another run-out chance and is he gone? It's gone to the third umpire. It was flatter outside off and they went for the single as soon as Waller pushed it on off. When the bail is dislodged, he looks in, but was out a frame before that. The replays are not very conclusive here and he's been given out! Williams stretched a lot there but looks like it wasn't enough. The third umpire took a long long time and we got a feeling he would be given not out for getting the benefit of the doubt but a brave decision from the umpire
on off again on length, defended on the front foot this time
on length on off again, defended on the front foot this time
on off, defended after leaning forward
on length on off, defended back to the bowler
fuller on off, driven back to Hafeez
flighted on middle, driven down to long-on
short of elngth on middle, Waller defended and an inside edge goes on the leg side
on length on middle, defended after leaning forward
full on the pads, pushed down to long-on
on length on middle, defended to cover
slightly slower on off and turning away, pushed on the off side
flatter on leg, turned to short fine leg
on length on off, pushed down to long-on
fuller on middle, turned away to deep square leg
full on off, defended towards point
tossed up outside off, defended back to Hafeez
short of length on middle, turned to midwicket
on length on off and turning in, defended on the front foot
on length on leg, defended after leaning forward
tossed up on middle, turned on off between extra cover and point
short of length on leg, sent to midwicket after a bounce from the back foot
shorter and flatter on off, pushed down to long-off for a single
slower on middle, Chigumbura defended but couldn't connect
quicker again on middle, defended well this time
short on middle, pulled to square leg
on length outside off, pushed back to Hafeez
low full toss on middle and leg, half-swept to deep fine leg
flighted and turning in from off, defended to cover
shorter outside off, defended on off side again
slower and well outside off, he went back and cut it well between extra cover and point for four
it was quick and darted in, but struck bat and pad almost at the same time so appeal is turned down
full on off, defended on the front foot
shorter legspinner on length, turned to short third man

gone this time! It was closer and would have hit the stumps. Afridi darted another one into the batsman, it pitched around off and came, Chigumbura defended but his bat didn't come down on time and the ball hit his pads right in front of the stumps just around the knee roll
quicker one on length on middle and leg, pushed to midwicket
fuller and straighter, defended back to Afridi
turning in form off, pushed to cover
on length on off, inside edge goes to square leg
shorter on off, turned towards square leg again
slower and slightly shorter on off and turning in, defended on the back foot
short of length and turning towards leg, steered to deep fine leg
flighted well outside off, driven to deep backward point
quick legspinner on off, defended on off from the back foot
slightly slower on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler
legspinner outside off, driven past cover
shorter one on off, pushed to cover off the back foot
a flighted wrong one on off, defended back to Afridi
flighted on off, driven past cover for a single
flighted outside off, Utseya defends but it went straight and missed the outside edge
off spinner coming in from outside off, defended after leaning forward
flighted well outside off again, he defended and was beaten again as it turned but not as much as he expected
flatter on middle, turned to square leg
flighted and beaten again! It was the doosra and he defended but missed it by a distance
turning in from off, defended on the off side
almost a yorker, driven down to long-on
quick and angled in, loud appeal for lbw but it was going down leg after pitching on middle
full and outside off, driven to the left of long-off
darted in from middle, turned square of the wicket on the leg side
full and wide, sends it past cover with a big drive
on length on off, defended on the off side
on length outside off, defended off the front foot
short and wide, cut past backward point
flighted outside off, he has driven it inside out over the covers for four to bring up the 100
on length outside off, defended to cover
another offspinner from outside off, defended towards cover
round the wicket, on length on off, defended to cover
full on middle, thick inside edge goes towards square leg
short of length on leg, turned to deep fine leg
quicker one on leg and angling in, sent to short fine leg
slightly slower on middle, thick inside edge goes to short fine leg
on length on off, pushed to cover
on length outside leg, Waller sweeps and there is a loud appeal for caught behind, but turned down by the umpire
on length on off, goes further away from the batsman and misses the outside edge
well outside off, pushed to cover
short of length on middle, the doosra is defended on the back foot
full outside off, driven straight to cover
slighted on length on leg, defended carefully
flighted on leg, swept in the air and it falls well short of deep fine leg
full on leg, defended to the left of midwicket
short of length outside off, cut to sweeper cover off the back foot
on length on middle, defended on the front foot
flighted legspinner on middle, defended again
legspinner outside off, Utseya went back and cut it well between sweeper cover and short third man for four
quicker and closer to off stump, cut wide of short third man
short of length on middle, turned to deep midwicket
flighted outside off, driven down to long-off
flighted outside off, beaten by the lack of turn
short of length on middle, whipped towards square leg
flighted outside off, driven down to long-on
full and marginally outside off, driven firmly down the ground to long-on
full on middle and leg, pushed down to long-off
full on middle, defended on the front foot
quicker one well outside leg and goes down further to beat the keeper also for four
short of length on leg, Utseya tries to turn it square and manages it
full on middle and leg, thick inside edge goes on the leg side
full, flighted and wide, driven to sweeper cover
quicker one outside leg again, another wide
flighted wrong on off, Waller defends and a thick inside edge goes towards midwicket
on length on off, Waller goes back and turns it on the leg side
on length outside off, pushed to point
on length outside off, Utseya was well inside the crease to defend it
similar delivery close to off, defended again
slightly wider and outside off, Utseya goes back and punches it through the covers in the gap for three
short of length on middle, Waller turns it past midwicket off the back foot
on length on off and angled away, Waller pokes and misses
on length well outside off, left alone
dropped at first slip. It was in the zone on off, Waller poked again and Hafeez dived to his right at slip but couldn't hold on to it
full well outside off, jabbed past point for a single
full well outside off and Waller crashes it thought the covers, it races away to the boundary, no half-measures this time
short of length on middle, defended on the of side for a single
quick outside off and Waller defends but misses
on length on leg, turned to the leg side
on length on off, pushed to cover for a quick single
short of length on off, slightly ballooned in the air after the defense
flighted outside off, pushed to cover
on length outside off, pushed to midwicket off the back foot
holds it back and the batsman pushes it off to long-off
angled down leg and he nudges it down to short fine where Irfan fields it safely
he's keeping it flat. Field restrictions must be playing on his mind as the batsman moves across to off and clips it off to midwicket
a little more air there and he comes onto the front foot to drive into the covers
he's getting more confident to toss the ball. The batsman pushes it into the off side off the front foot

Oh mix up there and he's run out! Holds this one back just a touch and the batsman stays at his crease, looking to work it square on the leg side. He can't make any contact as the ball dribbles down to short third man. The batsman sets off for a single but the fielder grabs the ball and throws it back with more than enough time for the keeper to remove the bails. Utseya trudges off and Zimbabwe lose an important wicket
The ball is tossed up outside off and is hit down the ground to long-off

cleans him up with the doosra. Brilliant bowling from Ajmal. Inviting flight draws the batsman forward into a defence that lacked conviction. The ball turns past the outside edge and crashes into top of off. Ajmal lives up to his nickname of Magician
oh, he loses his direction there. The ball is way down the leg side and it is pushed off behind square leg for a single
nicely flighted on middle and Waller comes forward and drives it down to long-on
tossed up again and the batsman comes forward, keeps his bat and pad together and blocks it
angled a little down leg and the batsman comes as far forward as he could to defend it into the off side
flatter and quicker this time and its picked off into the midwicket region. The batsmen look for a single but there isn't one and they're back just in time
clipped into the leg side again as Zimbabwe keep the scoreboard ticking, even if the boundaries aren't coming

top edge and Rehman yells a loud "mine" and takes it safely. Another wicket in the infamous Powerplay. Fuller ball on middle forces the Panyangara to go for the sweep but he is nowhere near the pitch of it and skies it. Rehman moves a few yards to his left and holds on to a relatively easy catch
fuller ball on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
attacks the stumps again and the batsman blocks it back to the bowler off his front foot
goes back in his crease and punches the shortish ball outside the off stump to long-off
goes back and opens the face to get a single into the point region
its the doosra again and Chatara doesn't pick it as he plays down the wrong line but gets hit on the pads
another doosra and this has greater bounce, leaping off a length to beat the outside edge of the batsman's intended defense
nudges it out to the leg side and scampers for a single
he comes forward to the full ball on the stumps and pushes it into the off side

and its all over. Ajmal gives this one a little air and bowling from around the wicket forces Waller to look to clip it into the leg side. The leading edge is taken and Abdur Rehman at point takes the simplest of catches. Pakistan win the deciding ODI and claim the series.
